From 1e6fb5f28c72ab4af031467e1a92f8c4aa5564b4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stefan Reinauer <stefan.reinauer@coreboot.org>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 18:10:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] build: disable QEMU 9 random provider for UAE

The QEMU 9 Win32 plugin runs inside WinUAE or FS-UAE as a loaded DLL.
QEMU's normal subsystem startup assumes it owns the process and can
terminate it if the crypto random provider cannot be initialized. That
is too aggressive for a plugin DLL.

The UAE PPC path does not need QEMU to provide guest cryptographic
random bytes during subsystem startup. Select QEMU's rng-none backend for
the QEMU 9 overlay so qcrypto_init() does not open the Windows crypto
provider just to bring up the Win32 plugin.
---
 configure-qemu-uae | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configure-qemu-uae b/configure-qemu-uae
index 591df4296c..d5452a2721 100755
--- a/configure-qemu-uae
+++ b/configure-qemu-uae
@@ -46,6 +46,7 @@ configure_qemu_uae() {
     --extra-cflags="$EXTRA_CFLAGS" \
     -Dqemu_uae=true \
     -Db_staticpic=true \
+    -Drng_none=true \
     --disable-werror \
     --disable-strip \
     --disable-tools \
-- 
